<HEAD>
<TITLE>ACLU - Sybil</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<blockquote>
<img src="/graphics/studenthdr.gif">
<center><h1>Who Is Sybil Liberty?</h1></center>
The Ask Sybil Liberty series of ACLU Briefers are designed to advise high
school and junior high school students about their rights in school.  Sybil
Liberty is a cartoon character who appears in both the electronic and print versions of the
publications in this section.
<P>
Sybil's basic message is that if we know and exercise our rights, we will be
better able to participate fully in the life of our nation. She suggests that
all students learn about the Bill of Rights and then speak out, organize and,
most importantly, get involved.
<P>
</blockquote>
<br><CENTER><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A><P>
