 	<HTML>
		<HEAD>	
		<TITLE>Stop Attacks on Reproductive Freedom
 </TITLE>
		</HEAD>
		<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
		<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/actionhdr.gif">

<center><img align="right" src ="/graphics/actnow.gif"><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Stop Attacks on Reproductive Freedom

</font></center>
<blockquote><font size = +2>A</font> nother attempt to ban a medically necessary abortion procedure is at the top of the Republican leadership's agenda for the 105th Congress. At issue is an abortion method known in the medical community as &quotdilation and extraction&quot(D&X) and &quotintact dialation and evacuation&quot (D&E) and misleadingly characterized by anti-choice legislators as &quotpartial-birth abortion.&quot

<p>During the ending days of the 104th Congress, both the House and Senate passed legislation that would ban so-called &quotpartial-birth abortions,&quot but President Clinton, listening to the experiences of women from around the country, vetoed the measure and an override attempt failed in the Senate.

<p>Proponents of the measure - called S. 6 this year -- are back again. Action on this legislation may occur soon. If we hope to prevail, we must act immediately.


</blockquote>
<center><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Oppose This Legislation</font></center>
<p>


<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">While nearly 90 percent of all abortions take place in the first twelve weeks of pregnancy, D&X is one of the safest methods available to preserve a woman's life, health and fertility of those women who need abortions later in pregnancy.

<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">Many of these women who need D&X make heart-wrenching decisions to end their pregnancies because of health risks to themselves or because of  fetal anomalies, some so serious that the fetus has no chance to survive outside of the womb.  Other women who have abortions after the first twelve weeks tend to be poor or young or both.  Their abortions are often delayed by funding bans or other legal barriers enacted by the same abortion opponents who are now callously trying to ban a safe, medically necessary procedure.    



<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">The proposed legislation would subject doctors who perform a D&X abortion to criminal prosecution. Physicians will be forced to weigh whether they should use a medical procedure they believe to be in the best interest of their patient and risk violating federal law and going to jail.


<p><center><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">TAKE ACTION NOW!</font></center>


<p>



<center><a href="http://www.aclu.org/cgi-bin/take_action.pl?GetDoc=118&dir=aclu&redirect=http://www.aclu.org/action/actthank.htm">Fax and Email your Senators and Representative</a></center><p>  
 We also have some <a href = "tips.html">tips</a> on lobbying your elected officials.
<p>


	<center>	<A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" 
		ISMAP BORDER=0></A>
