 	<HTML>
		<HEAD>	
		<TITLE>Letter to Senators Opposing School Voucher Legislation </TITLE>
		</HEAD>
		<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
		<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/actionhdr.gif">

<center><img align="right" src ="/graphics/actnow.gif"><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Taxpayer Subsidies For Religious Schools</font></center>
<blockquote><font size = +2>T</font>
 he very first bill offered by Senate Republicans in the 105th Congress is S. 1, the so-called "Safe and Affordable Schools Act." At its core is a school voucher scheme that would use taxpayer dollars to fund religious schools. These vouchers, which are also at the top of the Christian Coalition's new legislative agenda, are being touted as "Hope and Opportunity Scholarships."</blockquote>
<center><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Oppose This Legislation</font></center>
<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">At its very core, the school voucher scheme would force federal taxpayers to support religious beliefs and practices with which they may strongly disagree. At the heart of this proposal is the Christian Coalition's goal of merging government and religion and having public funds diverted to private and parochial schools.
<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">This legislation purports to help underprivileged youth in substandard public schools. But in reality, this proposal would abandon our local public schools. That's why groups that have traditionally advocated for improvement of public schools, such as the NAACP and the national PTA, oppose vouchers for parochial and private schools as do 61 percent of Americans surveyed in a recent Gallup poll.
<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">The proposed amount for vouchers in the last Congress was $3,000 per student. The median cost for a private school is $10,300 per year, meaning that private schools would still be out of reach of the poor. Thus, under the pretense of aiding the poor, voucher proponents are paving the way for their ultimate goal to subsidize religious education for wealthier families and leave poor students with no hope and no opportunity.

<p><center><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">TAKE ACTION NOW!</font></center>

<a href="http://www.aclu.org/cgi-bin/take_action.pl?GetDoc=114&dir=aclu&redirect=http://www.aclu.org/action/actthank.htm"><center>Fax and email your Senators</center></a><p>

<br clear = "all">
  




	<center>	<A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" 
		ISMAP BORDER=0></A>
		<P><H6><I>Copyright 1996, The American Civil Liberties 
		Union</I></H6></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
	   

