<head>
<title>EXPRESS YOURSELF: THE FIRST AMENDMENT</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>
<blockquote>
<img src="/graphics/studenthdr.gif">
<h2><center>
EXPRESS YOURSELF: THE FIRST AMENDMENT</center></h2>
<p>

"Express Yourself: The First Amendment," a unique interactive
software program for use on Macintosh compatible computers,
explores First Amendment issues as they relate to students today. 
The educational software is a tool to enable and empower young
people to learn more about their rights and then use them.  A
diverse team of students, teachers, activists, lawyers, and
constitutional scholars, brought together by the American Civil
Liberties Union of Northern California, shaped the program.  Red
Dot Interactive, a San Francisco-based team of interactive
software designers, utilized video, animation, music, graphics,
and text to bring this lively and innovative learning tool to
life.
<p>
The program was created by the ACLU-NC's Howard A. Friedman
First Amendment Education Project, a special five-year effort
focusing on student's rights.  The goal of the Friedman Project
is to work with high school students and teachers on issues
involving freedom of expression; freedom of the press; rights to
associate, assemble and petition the government; and freedom of
religion.  The project organizes special conferences, develops
materials and sends speakers into school classrooms in Northern
California.
<p>
"Express Yourself: The First Amendment," is available for download 
and is also distributed on a 3 1/2" diskette for
a cost of $10.00. Express Yourself is FREE to students only.  To order or
request a copy, please write to Express Yourself, Public Education
Department, American Civil Liberties Union, 132 West 43rd Street, New York,
NY 10036.
<p>
ALL INDIVIDUALS ARE ENCOURAGED TO COPY THE PROGRAM AND PASS IT ON
TO AS MANY OTHERS AS THEY WISH.
<p>
If you are interested in obtaining more information about the Friedman
Project, please send a letter to the ACLU-NC, 1663 Mission Street, Suite 460,
San Francisco, CA  94103.
<p>
<b>EXPRESS YOURSELF: Version 1.5  The National Version</b>
<p>
The original Express Yourself cited some laws and court rulings that are
specific to California, but version 1.5 has been updated to cover all of the
United States.  Consult your local ACLU affiliate for more information about
the law in your own state. 
<p>
<b><a href="ftp://ftp.newmedium.com/public/aclu/ExpressY.hqx">DOWNLOADING EXPRESS YOURSELF</a></b>
<p>
Express Yourself is a compressed HyperCard stack. <a href="ftp://ftp.newmedium.com/public/aclu/readme.txt">Download the readme file</a> for installation instructions, system requirements and special instructions for older Macs
that appear at the end of this description.
<p>
Express Yourself
The First Amendment
brought to you by
The ACLU of Northern California
<p>
Designed and Produced by Red Dot Interactive, Inc.
<p>
(c) 1995 ACLU of Northern California
<p>
