<HEAD><TITLE>
Internet Resources -- Women's Rights
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/women.gif">
</CENTER>
<P>
</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The following sites provide comprehensive or unique resources relating to
the work of the ACLU in this issue area.  While some of these sites are operated
by organizations that work frequently in coalition with the ACLU, the sites may
also include materials on positions we do not share. 
</P>
<P>To report a broken or relocated link, or to suggest a site for inclusion on
this page, use the feedback button at the bottom of this page. </P></BLOCKQUOTE><IMG
SRC="/../graphics/rbline.gif" WIDTH="100%">
<P>
<B><A HREF="http://www.feminist.org">Women's WebWorld -- The Feminist Majority
Online</A></B>  <BR> A comprehensive women's issues site on the Internet, the
Feminist Majority Online offers a wealth of information on all aspects of 
women's rights.  Feminist Majority publications, such as newsletters and special
reports, are available in hypertext versions.  In addition, several hundred
links to other women's issues sites are described and organized under seven
categories: General Women's Issues Sites, Women's Health (includes Abortion
Rights), Women &amp; Girls in Sports, Women and Work, Global Feminism, Women in
Politics, and Violence Against Women (includes Abortion Clinic Violence).  There
are also numerous Take Action! opportunities, special student and faculty
databases, several listings of hotlines, and a daily Feminist News section. 
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>
 
<B><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/women/feminist.html">Feminist Activist
Resources on the Net</A></B>  <BR>With about 100 links, this site covers the
gamut of women's issues, with sections like Sexual Harassment and Rape, Women
and Work, Women's Resources, Feminist Activist Calendar, and even Feminist Fun
and Games. </P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>
 
<B><A HREF="http://www.ibd.nrc.ca/~mansfield/feminism.html">Feminism and
Women's Resources</A></B>  <BR>Over 50 links to newsgroups, resources, and
organizations can be found at this site. 
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER> 
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.rochester.edu/SBA/index.html">Susan B. Anthony 
University Center -- University of Rochester</A></B>
<BR>This substantial site is a good example of the growing number of web sites
that choose to focus on one geographical region, in this case upstate New York. 
It contains information about community resources, the women's studies program,
Internet resources, and historical offerings.  In addition, it links to pages on
the  <A HREF="http://www.rochester.edu/SBA/hall.htm">National Women's Hall of
Fame</A> and <A HREF="http://www.rochester.edu/SBA/park.htm">
Women's Rights National Park</A>. 
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.now.org/">National Organization for Women
</A></B>
<BR>NOW's homepage contains a comprehensive array of information about the
organization.  Sections include the national editions of NOW Times, a breakdown
by topic area of issues NOW is involved in, and photos/profiles of NOW's
National Officers.</P>  
