<HEAD><TITLE>
ACLU Abolitionist (A NEWSLETTER ON THE NATIONWIDE STRUGGLE AGAINST THE DEATH PENALTY) - January 1996 
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<center>
<img src="/graphics/death.gif">
</center>
<P>
<blockquote>
<h2>THE FEDERAL DEATH PENALTY </h2>
<p>
While the death penalty has been left primarily to the states, 
recent imposition of federal death sentences on two men in Texas
shows the federal government intends to rival the states in its 
expanded use.  Between 1963 and 1994 the federal government
imposed death on 6 persons.  All were sentenced under the 1988 
Anti-Drug Abuse Act, signed into law by President Bush.  It allows 
the death penalty for a defendant who intentionally kills in the course 
of committing a felony drug offense.
<p>
     But the 1988 law can't hold a candle to the Federal Death Penalty 
Act (FDPA) signed into law by President Clinton in September 1994, 
which allows the death penalty for about 60 offenses.  Twenty two 
capital prosecutions have been authorized under this law since its 
enactment, with the first two death sentences announced last month. 
In the same time frame another 8 cases were prosecuted under the 
1988 law.  While the scope of federal death prosecutions is still far 
smaller than that in the states, only the tip of the iceberg may be 
visible as yet, for the FDPA authorizes the death penalty for just 
about any murder. 
<p>
     The intent of the federal hangmen is signalled by the implementation 
of the FDPA, the increase in prosecution under the Act, and the attempt 
in this Congressional session to provide statutory authority for a 
centralized federal death row in Terre Haute, Indiana.  The latter was 
(so far!) halted, in part through the efforts of the ACLU, the National 
Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers and others.  For an analysis 
of the FDPA, call Travia.
<p>
      --- <i>Hunter Labovitz and Theresa Fuentas</i>
<P><center><a href="abol196.html">Newsletter Index</a></center>
<p>
</blockquote>
<br>
<CENTER><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A><P>
