  <HEAD><TITLE>
ACLU Abolitionist (A NEWSLETTER ON THE NATIONWIDE STRUGGLE AGAINST THE DEATH PENALTY) - January 1996 
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<center>
<img src="/graphics/death.gif">
</center>
<P>
<blockquote>
   <h2>SUPREME COURT WATCH</h2>
<p>
On January 9 the Court will hear arguments in Loving v. United States, 
which focuses on the military death penalty.  The issue in Loving is 
whether the President has the constitutional power to prescribe death 
eligible crimes under the Uniform Code of Military Justice.  The ACLU 
filed an amicus brief in the case.  
<p>
Other cases before the court include Lonchar v. Thomas (argued 
December 4). and Cooper v. Oklahoma (scheduled for January 16).  A 
description of these cases and the Court's decision will be discussed 
in upcoming issues.  
<p>
<center><a href="abol196.html">Newsletter Index</a></center>
<p>
</blockquote>
