<HEAD>
<TITLE>Bill Hildebrand & Rev. Bob Moore Story</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>
<blockquote>
<img src="/graphics/courthdr.gif">
<CENTER><H2>ACLU Clients - Bill Hildebrand & Rev. Bob Moore</H2></CENTER>
<font size=4>
<img src="/graphics/billbob.jpg" align=left> <blockquote>As members of a coalition organized to protest the Gulf War, Bill and Bob
were prevented from distributing anti-war leaflets in a shopping mall by
security guards who said leafletting was not permitted.  In their
groundbreaking ACLU lawsuit, the state supreme court ruled that leafletting
in shopping malls is protected by the state's constitution.</font>
</blockquote>
<P><br clear=all><br>

</blockquote>    


