<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The following sites provide comprehensive or unique resources relating to
the work of the ACLU in this issue area.  While some of these sites are operated
by organizations that work frequently in coalition with the ACLU, the sites may
also include materials on positions we do not share. 
</P>
<P>To report a broken or relocated link, or to suggest a site for inclusion on
this page, use the feedback button at the bottom of this page. 
</P></BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/../graphics/rbline.gif" WIDTH="100%">
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.fga.com:80/aaaa/">American Association for Affirmative
Action</A></B>
<BR>AAAA, dedicated to &quot;the advancement of affirmative action, equal
opportunity and elimination of discrimination in the workplace,&quot; has
created a site filled with links to related articles and legislation, with
general information on the AAAA as well.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P><B><A HREF="http://www-leland.stanford.edu/group/King/">Martin Luther
King, Jr.</A></B>
<BR>This site, under construction, contains information on the MLK Papers
Project at Stanford University, and also draws from the King Estate and King
Center.  Users need to register to view some documents, with audio and video
files also available.  
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>
<B><A HREF="http://www.webcom.com/~justcaus/">JustCause Home Page</A></B>
<BR>JustCause, an organization promoting diversity, has action alerts,
articles, and links.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.nul.org/">The National Urban League</A></B>
<BR>The National Urban League, with the mission of assisting &quot;African
Americans in the achievement of social and economic equality,&quot; has general
League information on its site.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/africanam/africanam.html">African American
Directory @IGC</A></B>
<BR>This site currently contains information on Hot Topics and a directory of
resources.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.wp.com/Hirsane/aaction.html">Judy's Affirmative Action
Page</A></B>
<BR>Subtitled &quot;The evolution of Affirmative Action, written by an
Affirmative Action Officer,&quot; the page traces affirmative action  through
each President, starting with LBJ.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P><B><A HREF="http://drum.ncat.edu/~drwww/civil.html"> Drum Policy guide</A></B>
The Drum Civil Rights Page has information on the history of the civil rights
movement as well as some other links.</P>  
