<HTML><HEAD><TITLE> Issues -- HIV/AIDS</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/aids.gif">
</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The following sites provide comprehensive or unique resources relating to
the work of the ACLU in this issue area.  While some of these sites are operated
by organizations that work frequently in coalition with the ACLU, the sites may
also include materials on positions we do not share. 
</P>
<P>To report a broken or relocated link, or to suggest a site for inclusion on
this page, use the feedback button at the bottom of this page. </P>
</BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/../graphics/rbline.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
<B><A HREF="http://www.aidsquilt.org/">AIDS Memorial Quilt Website</A></B> 
<BR>This takes full advantage of the Internet's capability for multimedia 
communications.  Users can view one of the first 12 panels of the more  32,000
panel quilt, or they can download information on how to make their  own panel. 
Other sections include HTML pointers, a list of local chapters and  affiliates
of the NAMES project, an issue of the quarterly newsletter,  and a section on
AIDS information on the Internet.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://app.cnidr.org/">AIDS Patents Project</A></B>  <BR>This
site contains a searchable database of  about 2000 patents relating to AIDS. 
Information about how  to search is also provided.  
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P><B><A HREF="http://www.aidsnyc.org/network">AIDS Treatment Data Network</A></B>
 <BR>This non-profit oganization headquartered in New York City  provides &quot;treatment
counseling and referrals to men, women and children and their care providers.&quot;
 The web site includes a directory  of clinical trials in the NY area, one-page
fact sheets, and a Network  database, regularly updated, that reports &quot;on
the availability of government and pharmaceutical sponsored AIDS treatments
nationwide.&quot;</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.cdcnac.org/">CDC Aids Clearinghouse</A></B>  <BR>The
Clearinghouse  bills itself as &quot;a comprehensive information service for
people working  in the fields of HIV prevention, care, and support.&quot; 
Information on such  CDC services as the National AIDS hotline, as well as an
order form for free CDC publications, are among the offerings of this site.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>
 
<B><A HREF="http://hwbbs.gbgm-umc.org/">Computerized AIDS Ministries</A></B> 
<BR>This organization proclaims &quot;There is more to living with AIDS than
AIDS.&quot; Its home page provides information on the CAMS BBS service, access
documents  for its FTP server, and a daily abstract of  news and journal
articles related to HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://gbgm-umc.org/related/lists/aids.html"> United
Methodist-Sponsored AIDS Home Pages and links</A></B>  <BR>This site provides a
listing of AIDS-related sites on the web, with a special section for sites
sponsored by the Ministries.  Links are described,  in most cases with a phrase
or two.</P> 
