</CENTER>
<P>
</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The following sites provide comprehensive or unique resources relating to
the work of the ACLU in this issue area.  While some of these sites are operated
by organizations that work frequently in coalition with the ACLU, the sites may
also include materials on positions we do not share. 
</P>
<P>To report a broken or relocated link, or to suggest a site for inclusion on
this page, use the feedback button at the bottom of this page. </P></BLOCKQUOTE><IMG
SRC="/../graphics/rbline.gif" WIDTH="100%">
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.tmn.com/cdf/index.html">Children's Defense Fund</A></B>
 <BR>The Children's Defense Fund &quot;exists to provide a strong and effective
voice for all the children of America who cannot vote, lobby, or speak out for
themselves.&quot;  The well-designed page includes information on projects, and
what you can do to help.  </P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.dnai.com/~children/">Children Now</A></B>
<BR>This online center for child activists has as its primary issues such
topics as Family Economic Security, Improving Our Schools, and Children and
Violence.  </P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.arcade.uiowa.edu/proj/ge/">Gender Equity in Sports</A></B>
 <BR>With about 20 links, this text-based site provides a comprehensive
examination of Title IX. </P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P> 
<B><A HREF="http://www.ai.mit.edu/people/ellens/NCRA/ncra.html">  National
Child Rights Allaince</A></B>
<BR>The NCRA, the only national organization directed entirely by youth and
adult survivors of abuse and neglect,  has links to around 20 pro-child rights
articles.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/syllabi?education">Supreme Court
Decisions on Education</A></B>
<BR>This section of the Cornell Law School Supreme Court site contains the
texts of decisions related to education.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.firn.edu/doe/eeop/eeop.html">Equal Educational
Opportunities Program Home Page</A></B>
<BR>EEOP provides &quot;services on a wide range of topics impacting
educational equity on the basis of race, gender, national origin, disability,
age and marital status.&quot; The site describes their publications and training
programs, and provides numerous links. 
</P>  
