 	<HTML>
		<HEAD>	
		<TITLE>Act Now - Legislation Addresses 'Driving While Black' Traffic Offense
</TITLE>
		</HEAD>
		<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
		<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/actionhdr.gif">

<center><img align="right" src ="/graphics/actnow.gif"><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Legislation Addresses 'Driving While Black' Traffic Offense

</font></center>
<blockquote><font size = +2>S</font> cores of African-American males - including prominent athletes, Members of Congress, actors and business leaders - have experienced the humiliation of being stopped on the nation's roads for no other reason than the alleged traffic offense derisively referred to as &quotDriving While Black.&quot

<p>Congressman John Conyers has proposed legislation that would begin to address this unjust practice. The "Traffic Stops Statistics Act of 1997" would encourage police departments to keep detailed records of traffic stops, including the race and ethnicity of the person stopped. The Justice Department would be charged with collecting the data and determining the full scope of this problem nationwide.
</blockquote>
<center><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Support This Legislation</font></center>
<p>
 <img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">One study of police stops on a strip of interstate in Maryland gives some insight into the nature of the problem. Over several-months in 1995, a survey found that 73 percent of the cars stopped and searched were driven by African-Americans, while they made up only 14 percent of the people driving along the interstate.


<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">While anecdotal evidence abounds, there has been no systematic effort to track this trend from a federal level. ACLU offices in Maryland, Illinois, Indiana and Florida, however, have found enough evidence to warrant federal or state lawsuits against police departments.


<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">This is exactly the sort of unequal treatment that leads minorities to distrust the criminal justice system.



<p><center><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">TAKE ACTION NOW!</font></center>


<p>This legislation has just been introduced, and so no action has been taken yet. One item that can help the prospects of a bill is the numbers of supporters, or co-sponsors, that have signed on to the bill.  Therefore, we want to encourage Members of Congress to sign onto the bill, so that we have as many cosponsors as possible.

<p><center><a href="http://www.aclu.org/cgi-bin/take_action.pl?GetDoc=116&dir=aclu&redirect=http://www.aclu.org/action/actthank.htm">Fax and Email your Representative</a></center><p>
 We also have some <a href = "tips.html">tips</a> on lobbying your elected officials.

<p>
<br clear = "all">
  




		<centeR><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" 
		ISMAP BORDER=0></A>
		<P><H6><I>Copyright 1996, The American Civil Liberties 
		Union</I></H6></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
	   





