<HEAD><TITLE>
Internet Resources -- Immigrant's Rights
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/immigrant.gif">
</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>The following sites provide comprehensive or unique resources
relating to the work of the ACLU in this issue area.  While some of these sites
are operated by organizations that work frequently in coalition with the ACLU,
the sites may also include materials on positions we do not share. 
</P>
<P>To report a broken or relocated link, or to suggest a site for inclusion on
this page, use the feedback button at the bottom of this page. </P>
</BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/../graphics/rbline.gif" WIDTH="100%">
<P>

<B><A HREF="gopher://garnet.berkeley.edu:1870/">Opposition to Proposition 187
Gopher</A></B>  <BR>This gopher site holds documents relevant to the fight
against Prop 187, including a collection of  articles, research studies, and
links to other immigrant rights gophers.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="ftp://heather.cs.ucdavis.edu/pub/Immigration/Index.html">Immigration
Forum</A></B>  <BR>This collection of links provides an overview of the
diversity of viewpoints on the topic of immigration, with much of the material
drawn from 'specialists in the field.' 
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>

<P>
<B><A HREF="http://www.law.cornell.edu/syllabi?illegal+immigration">Supreme

Court Cases on Immigration</A></B>
<BR>This collection of documents is drawn from Cornell Law School's collection
of hypertexted Supreme Court decisions.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="http://www.telalink.net/~gsiskind/bulletin.html">Immigration
Bulletin, by Siskind and Susser</A></B>
<BR>This Immigration and Nationality law firm has put their monthly bulletin --
tracking legal developments in the field -- online, and made it browsable by
both issue and title.
</P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/../graphics/redline.gif" WIDTH="50%"></CENTER>
<P>

<B><A HREF="gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org/11/peace/immig.gopher">Immigrant and
Refugee Rights Gopher</A></B>
<BR>This gopher site links to files on militarizing our borders, immigrant
rights publications, and the Immigrant and Refugee Rights Network on PeaceNet.
</P>
