<BLOCKQUOTE>


<H3><CENTER>Banned Books Week</CENTER></H3>

Books are banned from public schools and libraries across the country. Censors normally give reasons they want books banned,
but it can be tough to understand the connection between the challenge
and the book.
<P>
In our quiz below we give you six quotes from censors, and 18 books that have been challenged or banned.
Can you guess which quote goes with which book?<P>


<FORM METHOD="POST" ACTION ="/cgi-bin/quiz.pl">
<INPUT TYPE="hidden" VALUE="aclu/bbw.cf" NAME="cf">
<INPUT TYPE="hidden" NAME="order" VALUE="one:two:three:four:five:six">

<TABLE BORDER="1" CELLPADDING="4" CELLSPACING="4" WIDTH="90%">
<TR>
	<TH width=30%>Quote </TH>
	<Th width=70%>List of Banned Books


<TR>
	<TD width=30%>"Condones the Use of Alcohol"</TD>
	<TD width=70%>


<input type="radio" name="one" value="The Grapes of Wrath"><U>The Grapes of Wrath</U>, by John Steinbeck<BR>
<input type="radio" name="one" value="Bell Jar"><U>The Bell Jar</U>, by Sylvia Plath<BR>
<input type="radio" name="one" value="Little Red Riding Hood"><U>Little Red Riding Hood</U>, traditional<BR>

<P>

</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
	<TD width=30%>"glorified Satan, suicide and cannibalism, and also encouraged children to be disobedient."</TD>
	<TD width=70%>


<input type="radio" name="two" value="Are You There God, It's Me, Margaret"><U>Are You There God, It's Me, Margaret</U>, by Judy Bloom<BR>
<input type="radio" name="two" value="A Light in the Attic"><U>A Light in the Attic</U>, by Shel Silverstein<BR>
<input type="radio" name="two" value="Revolting Rhymes"><U>Revolting Rhymes</U>, by Roald Dahl<BR>

<P>

</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD width=30%>"garbage being passed off as literature"</TD>
	<TD width=70%>


<input type="radio" name="three" value="Canterbury Tales"><U>Canterbury Tales</U>, by Chaucer<BR>
<input type="radio" name="three" value="One Hundred Years of Solitude"><U>One Hundred Years of Solitude</U>, by Gabriel Garcia-Marquez<BR>
<input type="radio" name="three" value="The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn"><U>The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn</U>, by Mark Twain<BR>

<P>

</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
	<TD width=30%>"criminalizes the foresting industry"</TD>
	<TD width=70%>


<input type="radio" name="four" value="The Giving Tree"><U>The Giving Tree</U>, by Shel Silverstein<BR>
<input type="radio" name="four" value="The House Without a Christmas Tree"><U>The House Without a Christmas Tree</U>, by Gail Rock<BR>
