not used in most developed countries.
 <p> <b>
 Question    :</b> If we are going to have executions should not they be on
television so America can see what a 'real' hanging or firing squad is like?
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> That question comes from KirkClyat.  Thank you.
 <p> <b>
 MikefDPF    :</b> There is blood and pain, the body loses control of its
functions and there is excrement and sweat and it is without dignity for any
and all involved.
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> This next question is from BigDogher.
 <p> <b>
 Question    :</b> What do we do with these individuals?  The prisons are full
now.  You can't argue that these people should not walk the streets again,
can you?
 <p> <b>
 MikefDPF    :</b> Some people can be transformed into useful citizens, of
course.  Others may not be.  We can and should separate dangerous, violent
people from society until they can behave properly.  Prisons today are
over-full of people who are not violent and who could be made to pay their
debt to society in more productive ways.
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Thank you Mike Farrell.  And, thank you Jensie Anderson
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Jensie is a staff attorney for the ACLU of Utah and joins us
from her home.  Thanks for being here.
 <p> <b>
 MikefDPF    :</b> Thanks, Kevin.  I'm willing to hang around for a few minutes
if you like.
 <p> <b>
 Jensieclu   :</b> Thank you.  It was an honor.
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Mike, don't go away just yet.  Goodbye Jensie and thanks again.
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Mike Farrell, actor and activist, has held vigil with the ACLU
for three hours now. John Albert Taylor was executed at 12 :07 a.m. in Utah
by firing squad.
 <p> <b>
 MikefDPF    :</b> I just want to have us think about Marie Deans' question.  Why
is it that we are so good at passing on violence and so poor at passing on love?
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Thanks you all for your questions and participation.
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Please be sure to check out the rest of the ACLU's
Constitution Hall at keyword ACLU.
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Mike, would you be willing to join the melee in the fully
interactive Free Speech Zone?
 <p> <b>
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Mike is considering moving over to the ACLU's interactive chat
room, the Free Speech Zone.
 <p> <b>
 Driley7     :</b> Of course, that is the decision everyone should make.   :)
  <p> <b>
KeenanCLU   :</b> Like he, all you will have to do is &quot;go to&quot; &quot;keyword&quot; &quot;ACLU&quot;
and enter the ACLU Live area.
<p> <b> 
 KeenanCLU   :</b> Thanks as well to David Riley who fielded your questions and
comments and brought you up here on stage.
 <p> <b>
 Driley7     :</b> Kevin, Mike... it was fun working with you.. and I want to
thank the members of our audience who joined us on stage  :)
 <p> <b>
 Driley7     :</b> Mike is in the Free Speech Zone... I guess if you want to see
his last words, you'll have to go there

</p>

</blockquote>


